00:14:21,650 --> 00:14:22,970
And they're not alone, pup.

318
00:14:31,390 --> 00:14:32,030
Stalker?

319
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:39,810
How did you get back in your ectoskeleton?

320
00:14:40,090 --> 00:14:41,090
What are you doing here?

321
00:14:41,350 --> 00:14:42,890
All excellent questions.

322
00:14:43,430 --> 00:14:43,870
Catch!

323
00:14:47,610 --> 00:14:49,790
Hey, I can't phase out of this.

324
00:14:50,270 --> 00:14:51,850
It's disrupting my powers.

325
00:14:52,030 --> 00:14:53,930
Then that's not all it does.

326
00:15:05,870 --> 00:15:07,630
The glowing blade is new.

327
00:15:07,930 --> 00:15:08,410
You like it?

328
00:15:08,630 --> 00:15:09,570
I've had some upgrades.

329
00:15:10,310 --> 00:15:10,830
No.

330
00:15:11,190 --> 00:15:11,490
Enough!

331
00:15:12,270 --> 00:15:14,450
I didn't free you to kill the boy,

332
00:15:14,590 --> 00:15:14,930
Skulker.

333
00:15:15,390 --> 00:15:16,310
Your work is done.

334
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:20,970
Yes, well, I've got to go to the

335
00:15:20,970 --> 00:15:22,610
library and check out a book on a

336
00:15:22,610 --> 00:15:22,910
gorilla.

337
00:15:23,470 --> 00:15:23,930
Again!

338
00:15:27,210 --> 00:15:27,730
Skulker?

339
00:15:28,230 --> 00:15:29,070
The ectopuses?

340
00:15:29,550 --> 00:15:30,570
I don't understand.

341
00:15:30,950 --> 00:15:31,810
Of course not.

342
00:15:31,910 --> 00:15:33,050
You're what, 14?

343
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:35,810
Too young to drive and not in college

344
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:36,110
yet?

345
00:15:36,430 --> 00:15:39,310
I sent those ghosts and others to test

346
00:15:39,310 --> 00:15:40,710
your father's skills.

347
00:15:41,390 --> 00:15:44,250
Imagine my surprise when I find you, the

348
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:47,350
second ghost hybrid his foolishness created.

349
00:15:47,670 --> 00:15:48,170
Second?

350
00:15:53,090 --> 00:15:53,810
You!

351
00:15:54,430 --> 00:15:55,670
I'm going ghost!

352
00:15:56,890 --> 00:15:57,850
Going ghost!

353
00:15:58,730 --> 00:16:00,390
Why can't I go ghost?

354
00:16:00,550 --> 00:16:01,590
You have a battle cry.

355
00:16:01,730 --> 00:16:02,230
Hilarious.

356
00:16:02,910 --> 00:16:05,630
I, on the other hand, have this.

357
00:16:06,310 --> 00:16:10,250
A spectral energy neutralizer designed by Skulker, paid

358
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:10,990
for by me.

359
00:16:11,350 --> 00:16:13,270
And as long as you're contained within that

360
00:16:13,270 --> 00:16:16,690
box, you're as human as your idiot father.

361
00:16:17,130 --> 00:16:18,190
Let me out of here!

362
00:16:18,590 --> 00:16:18,990
Why?

363
00:16:19,370 --> 00:16:21,430
So you can go back to stumbling through

364
00:16:21,430 --> 00:16:24,250
your adolescence, desperately trying to get control of

365
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:24,910
your powers?

366
00:16:25,190 --> 00:16:27,150
Powers, by the way, that I've had for

367
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:28,350
20 years.

368
00:16:28,710 --> 00:16:30,970
I have experience, my child.

369
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:33,410
And the money and power I've gained through

370
00:16:33,410 --> 00:16:36,350
using those powers for personal gain, you see.

371
00:16:36,690 --> 00:16:39,170
I could train you, teach you everything I

372
00:16:39,170 --> 00:16:42,570
know, and all you'd have to do is

373
00:16:42,570 --> 00:16:45,010
renounce your idiot father.

374
00:16:45,530 --> 00:16:48,930
Dude, you are one seriously crazed up Froot

375
00:16:48,930 --> 00:16:49,150
Loop.

376
00:16:49,450 --> 00:16:51,630
That is never going to happen.

377
00:16:51,870 --> 00:16:54,070
Yes, well, once your father is out of

378
00:16:54,070 --> 00:16:55,950
the way, we'll see how you feel.

379
00:17:03,569 --> 00:17:06,710
Then I covered the gorilla uprising in Umakistan.

380
00:17:06,910 --> 00:17:08,770
Got an exclusive with the rebel leader that

381
00:17:08,770 --> 00:17:09,710
got raves.

382
00:17:10,210 --> 00:17:11,829
Am I boring you, Jack?

383
00:17:12,050 --> 00:17:13,190
Frankly, yes.

384
00:17:18,829 --> 00:17:20,869
So, what do you say we liven up

385
00:17:20,869 --> 00:17:21,790
this shindig?

386
00:17:22,170 --> 00:17:22,410
Hey!

387
00:17:26,690 --> 00:17:30,670
Jack, what's the matter with you?

388
00:17:31,010 --> 00:17:33,370
Why, Maddie, didn't you always know I'd turn

389
00:17:33,370 --> 00:17:33,950
on you?

390
00:17:33,950 --> 00:17:36,550
That when you chose me, you chose wrong.

391
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:37,230
Get out.

392
00:17:37,850 --> 00:17:38,770
Get out of me.

393
00:17:39,230 --> 00:17:41,410
I don't know what's come over you, but

394
00:17:41,410 --> 00:17:43,890
when I write about this, I swear...

395
00:17:43,890 --> 00:17:43,990
Ghost!

396
00:17:44,130 --> 00:17:44,810
Overpowering me.

397
00:17:45,390 --> 00:17:46,610
Maddie, run.

398
00:17:48,190 --> 00:17:49,410
He's a ghost?

399
00:17:49,930 --> 00:17:52,290
This is the story of the century.

400
00:17:52,650 --> 00:17:54,250
Come on, we have to get to the

401
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:55,990
Fenton family ghost assault vehicle.

402
00:17:56,890 --> 00:17:57,870
I mean, the RV.

403
00:17:59,990 --> 00:18:02,450
Well, gosh and golly, it looks like you

404
00:18:02,450 --> 00:18:04,350
could use a speck of help there, don't

405
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:04,890
you know?

406
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:07,130
Hey, you're the Dairy King.

407
00:18:07,590 --> 00:18:08,290
Oh, great.

408
00:18:08,850 --> 00:18:10,650
What are you gonna do, suffocate me with

409
00:18:10,650 --> 00:18:13,530
Limburger, strangle me with Swiss, or...

410
00:18:16,810 --> 00:18:18,230
Let me go.

411
00:18:20,090 --> 00:18:22,050
Thank you, but why?

412
00:18:22,290 --> 00:18:24,430
Not all ghosts are evil, right?

413
00:18:24,810 --> 00:18:26,550
Some of us just want to be left

414
00:18:26,550 --> 00:18:28,090
alone there, don't you know?

415
00:18:28,470 --> 00:18:30,690
Hey, will you help me fight Plasmius?

416
00:18:30,850 --> 00:18:32,610
I'm the Dairy King, kiddo.

417
00:18:32,870 --> 00:18:33,850
Kings don't fight.

418
00:18:34,090 --> 00:18:36,370
They send other people to fight farmers.

419
00:18:37,030 --> 00:18:39,530
Royalty 101 there, don't you know?

420
00:18:41,550 --> 00:18:43,910
It's Dairy Fresh...

421
00:18:43,910 --> 00:18:44,410
Jack!

422
00:18:44,670 --> 00:18:45,150
Dad!

423
00:18:51,330 --> 00:18:54,330
So, Maddie, when did you first realize your

424
00:18:54,330 --> 00:18:56,710
husband was a monster bent on destroying his

425
00:18:56,710 --> 00:18:58,850
smarter, more successful, and better-dressed peers?

426
00:18:59,130 --> 00:19:00,630
What are you talking about?

427
00:19:00,830 --> 00:19:02,850
That jumpsuit is incredibly stylish.

428
00:19:09,110 --> 00:19:11,630
I'm guessing we won't be invited back.

429
00:19:14,090 --> 00:19:16,090
If you live to tell the tale, remember

430
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:18,630
that big, fat Jack Fenton did this to

431
00:19:18,630 --> 00:19:18,930
you?

432
00:19:19,190 --> 00:19:20,650
Yes, again, cheese head.

433
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:31,440
Nobody uses Jack Fenton as a human meat

434
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:31,740
puppet.

435
00:19:37,220 --> 00:19:38,160
Daniel, stop.

436
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:39,820
Think about the things I could show you.

437
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:41,880
The doors I could open for you.

438
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:46,780
You, Danny Phantom, and I, Vlad Plasmius, together

439
00:19:46,780 --> 00:19:48,080
we could rule.

440
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:49,320
Forget it, pal.

441
00:19:49,460 --> 00:19:51,400
Your money can't buy my mom, it can't

442
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,680
buy the Packers, and it can't buy me.

443
00:19:59,360 --> 00:20:00,700
I know who you are.

444
00:20:00,940 --> 00:20:01,880
I'll tell my father.

445
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:03,380
I'll tell everyone.

446
00:20:03,860 --> 00:20:04,900
And so will I.

447
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:09,080
Honestly, if you expose me, you expose yourself.

448
00:20:15,460 --> 00:20:17,020
Mind if I cut in?

449
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:20,020
Let go of me.

450
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:21,780
Never again, woman.

451
00:20:27,360 --> 00:20:29,220
Oh, great, it's a stick.

452
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:31,180
And I wasn't going to come to this

453
00:20:31,180 --> 00:20:31,500
thing.

454
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:35,480
Jack, look out!

455
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:35,980
The RV!

456
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:42,320
Sorry, Dad, I've got one shot at this.

457
00:21:04,310 --> 00:21:06,070
Jack, you did it!

458
00:21:06,250 --> 00:21:07,310
It was nothing, Mom.

459
00:21:07,610 --> 00:21:08,530
Uh, Maddie?

460
00:21:08,890 --> 00:21:09,890
Sure, Maddie.

461
00:21:10,290 --> 00:21:12,410
You make sure Harry's okay while I finish

462
00:21:12,410 --> 00:21:12,750
this.

463
00:21:15,450 --> 00:21:17,190
How's it going, V-Man?

464
00:21:17,750 --> 00:21:19,610
Oh, you've overshadowed Jack.

465
00:21:19,790 --> 00:21:21,210
Oh, I'm so scared.

466
00:21:21,310 --> 00:21:22,150
Now, what's next?

467
00:21:22,330 --> 00:21:23,210
A card trick?

468
00:21:23,410 --> 00:21:23,930
Listen to me.

469
00:21:24,250 --> 00:21:26,090
I swear I'll walk out of my dad

470
00:21:26,090 --> 00:21:28,870
right now and expose us both, unless you

471
00:21:28,870 --> 00:21:29,810
agree to a truce.

472
00:21:30,150 --> 00:21:31,630
You're bluffing.

473
00:21:31,730 --> 00:21:32,330
No, I'm not.

474
00:21:32,850 --> 00:21:35,010
My parents will accept me, no matter what.

475
00:21:35,150 --> 00:21:38,490
But if I expose you, well, what would

476
00:21:38,490 --> 00:21:39,790
my mom think of you?

477
00:21:40,790 --> 00:21:43,490
You'll be miserable and alone for the rest

478
00:21:43,490 --> 00:21:46,210
of your life, unless you call a truce.

479
00:21:46,530 --> 00:21:49,590
Using your opponent's weaknesses against him.

480
00:21:49,950 --> 00:21:52,070
I am teaching you something, after all, very

481
00:21:52,070 --> 00:21:52,530
well.

482
00:21:53,170 --> 00:21:53,830
Truce.

483
00:21:54,150 --> 00:21:57,170
Eventually, you will join me by choice, you

484
00:21:57,170 --> 00:21:57,890
and your mother.

485
00:21:58,530 --> 00:21:59,240
But for now...

486
00:22:00,910 --> 00:22:02,730
Curse you, Jack Fenton!

487
00:22:03,170 --> 00:22:06,530
Your world-renowned expertise of all things ghost

488
00:22:06,530 --> 00:22:08,390
has defeated me.

489
00:22:09,370 --> 00:22:12,070
Until next time, son.

490
00:22:18,290 --> 00:22:19,910
World-renowned expertise.

491
00:22:20,770 --> 00:22:21,310
Outstanding.

492
00:22:21,790 --> 00:22:24,910
Jack, I have never seen you like this.

493
00:22:25,070 --> 00:22:26,870
You beat that ghost all the way to

494
00:22:26,870 --> 00:22:27,630
Kenosha.

495
00:22:28,110 --> 00:22:28,670
I did?

496
00:22:28,990 --> 00:22:30,470
Oh, heck, I'm just doing my job.

497
00:22:31,510 --> 00:22:32,590
And mine.

498
00:22:32,970 --> 00:22:34,810
Jack, for all the years I thought you

499
00:22:34,810 --> 00:22:36,950
were a crackpot, I sort of apologize.

500
00:22:37,710 --> 00:22:38,250
Ghosts!

501
00:22:38,390 --> 00:22:40,070
This story will make your career.

502
00:22:40,370 --> 00:22:41,170
And mine.

503
00:22:44,050 --> 00:22:45,910
I can't believe they fired Harry.

504
00:22:46,170 --> 00:22:47,590
Of course they fired her.

505
00:22:47,850 --> 00:22:50,070
She tried to file some crackpot story about

506
00:22:50,070 --> 00:22:50,650
ghosts.

507
00:22:50,950 --> 00:22:54,170
It's the Milwaukee Journal, not the National Enquirer.

508
00:22:55,210 --> 00:22:57,550
I can't believe Harry blames me.

509
00:22:58,190 --> 00:22:59,770
And Vlad was so mad, he didn't even

510
00:22:59,770 --> 00:23:00,390
say goodbye.

511
00:23:01,150 --> 00:23:02,870
And we were all such great chums in

512
00:23:02,870 --> 00:23:03,250
college.

513
00:23:04,290 --> 00:23:04,810
Whatever.

514
00:23:05,490 --> 00:23:06,850
Who cares what you were when you were

515
00:23:06,850 --> 00:23:07,190
younger?

516
00:23:07,190 --> 00:23:09,230
It's who you grew into that makes you

517
00:23:09,230 --> 00:23:09,830
who you are.

518
00:23:09,990 --> 00:23:10,370
You think?

519
00:23:10,590 --> 00:23:12,630
Hey, if you can cause that much damage

520
00:23:12,630 --> 00:23:14,470
in college, and still turn out to be

521
00:23:14,470 --> 00:23:17,770
this cool, ghost-butt-kicking adult, well, maybe

522
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:18,750
there's hope for me yet.

523
00:23:18,890 --> 00:23:19,770
Thanks, son.

524
00:23:20,450 --> 00:23:21,750
But your curfew is still ten.

525
00:23:22,050 --> 00:23:23,150
Oh, man.
